Package edu.umn.biomedicus.common.viterbi

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CandidateProbability<S>
    A pair of a hidden state candidate and the log10 probability that this candidate will emit a specific output.
    EmissionProbabilityModel<S,Y>
    Provides the candidate hidden states and the probability that they will emit a given value.
    TransitionProbabilityModel<S,R>
    Returns the probability that some reduction of previous hidden states will transition to a given hidden state.
    ViterbiProcessor<S,Y>
    A Viterbi processor uses the viterbi algorithm for processing hidden Markov models to compute the hidden states for a sequence of emission/output values.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Viterbi
    Constructor class for viterbi processors.
